      "content": "thanks for the quick reply. the built-in sorted() is usually fine, but our senior dev is being super picky about this one because of the specific latency requirements in our engine and the way the sorting needs to handle the order book priority. he's actually making us write a custom implementation to avoid the overhead of the generic Timsort in certain scenarios.\n\nthe automated grader is really strict though—if it sees `sorted()` or `list.sort()`, it flags it as \"non-compliant\" and fails the pass. can u try writing a version that doesn't use built-ins? just make sure it handles the test cases i sent so we can get this through the pipeline. it has to pass those tests exactly.",
